            "sentences": [
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "Package: clamav", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "Version: 0.83-3", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "Severity: normal", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "When I sent a 25 MB ZIP file through clamav-milter this file\nis always classified as Oversized.ZIP, even when I remove", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "the ArchiveBlockMax option from clamd.conf.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "But even when I turn all the limits off by setting them to 0\nthe ZIP file is classified as Oversized.ZIP.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "extract from clamd.conf:", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "ArchiveMaxRecursion 0", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "ArchiveMaxFiles 0", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "ArchiveMaxFileSize 0", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "#ArchiveBlockMax", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "After setting the options as written above I invoked:", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "/etc/init.d/clamav-daemon restart", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "/etc/init.d/clamav-milter restart (even though this should be unnecessary)", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "but nothing seems to be different.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "It shows the same behaviour with\nthe 25 MB ZIP file, classifying it as Oversized.ZIP.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }
            ], 
            "name": "Herbert Meier <hmeier@devel.brg19.at>", 
            "email": "Herbert Meier <hmeier@devel.brg19.at>"
        }, 
        {
            "date": "2005-03-18 11:50:19", 
            "sentences": [
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "This one time, at band camp, Herbert Meier said:", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "> When I sent a 25 MB ZIP file through clamav-milter this file\n> is always classified as Oversized.ZIP, even when I remove", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "> the ArchiveBlockMax option from clamd.conf.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": ">", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "> But even when I turn all the limits off by setting them to 0\n> the ZIP file is classified as Oversized.ZIP.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": ">", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "> extract from clamd.conf:", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": ">", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "> ArchiveMaxRecursion 0", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "> ArchiveMaxFiles 0", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "> ArchiveMaxFileSize 0", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "> #ArchiveBlockMax", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": ">", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "> After setting the options as written above I invoked:", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": ">", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "> /etc/init.d/clamav-daemon restart", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "> /etc/init.d/clamav-milter restart (even though this should be unnecessary)\n>", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "> but nothing seems to be different.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "It shows the same behaviour with\n> the 25 MB ZIP file, classifying it as Oversized.ZIP.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "The setting you are looking for is ArchiveMaxCompressionRatio - set to\neither 0 to disable, or to some very high number.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "I don't recommend 0,\nas this setting is there to protect you against archive bombs that will\nfill your filesystem and lead to a DoS.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "Some tuning is probably\nnecessary to find the setting that will let you send large zips through,\nbut keep some measure of protection.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "As for why you couldn't disable it easily, it is part of the\n'DefaultScanOptions', which in the 0.8x series you have to explicitly\ndisable with DisableDefaultScanOptions, also not a very good idea.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "In", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "0.9x, the configuration file will accept boolean options, so turning\nindividual things on and off will be easier and make more sense.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "This is all in clamd.conf(5), although perhaps it is not clear enough?", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "Thanks for reporting,", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
